main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a single orange flashing object in the sky in Hartford, Wisconsin in June 1966.
interesting points: The object flashed on and off every two seconds.
The object went out of sight behind some trees in front of the observer.
The observer reported that the object appeared to stand still at times and suddenly speed up and rush away.
The observer estimated the size of the object to be about the size of a match head or slightly larger.
The observer described the object as appearing to be a disc, but not very distinctive in its shape.
sighted object: a single orange flashing object in the sky
